cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.DC 

This paper focuses on traffic engineering in Software-Defined Networks (SDN), which is a subfield of computer networking. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a new approach to clustering traffic data, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The paper also deals with the problem of network reconfiguration, which can be seen as a control problem, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. The paper also discusses the issue of network security, which can be related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of network resources, which can be related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
